    <p>
        The <code>--context DB</code> flag is required because the project defines
        more than one <code>DbContext</code> (the app's main <code>DB</code> context
        and a separate one used only by Cosmos replication). Without specifying which
        one, the EF tools will refuse to proceed.
    </p>

    <DocCallout Type="DocCalloutType.Tip">
        If you ever modify your entities later (add a property, add an entity, change
        a relationship), repeat this step with a different migration name —
        <code>dotnet ef migrations add AddProductCategoryColor --context DB ...</code> — and
        then re-run Step 3 below.
    </DocCallout>
</DocSection>

